  <bioghist encodinganalog="545"> 
    <head>Biography of Robert S. Anderson</head><p>Robert S. Anderson and a group of friends from Butte, Montana, attempted to develop petroleum prospects in the Devil’s Basin area of Montana in 1916. The group organized the Montana Cycle Oil Company, invested money to bring in geologist Gordon Campbell, and leased about 12,000 acres. Although a drilling rig was brought in, the under-capitalized association was unable to find profitable oil.</p>
	 
  </bioghist> 
  <scopecontent encodinganalog="520"> 
    <head>Scope and Content</head><p>The collection contains letters, telegrams, and a geological report from Gordon Campbell; legal agreements, leases, and other documents; promotional material for the Montana Cycle Oil Company and the Montana-Canadian Oil Company; and reminiscences from Robert S. Anderson about the activities of the men who formed the Montana Cycle Oil Company.</p>
	 
  </scopecontent> 
